title: Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec Moulin Rouge, La Goulue Unmatted Print
description:
Print developed from Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec’s Moulon Rouge, La Goulue, 1891, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Moulin Rouge, La Goulue (1891) was Toulouse-Lautrec’s first commissioned poster, created to advertise the performance of dancer La Goulue and acrobat Valentin le Desossé at the iconic Montmartre dance hall.

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image size:  11 x 14 in.
  • Full poster size:  12 x 16 in.
  • Materials: Premium Cardstock
